cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a novel structure for unsupervised conditional GANs and evaluates its performance on the task of disentangling latent variables. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and graphics (cs.GR). However, given the focus on generative models and image generation, we believe that cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
